  "number": 359,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/359",
  "title": "Widget proposal: clearAll",
  "body": "It would be good to be able to have a very simple widget that allows you to clear all the refinements and current query.\n\nIt's like a \"start over\" button in case of emergency/lost user.\n# API\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.hitsPerPageSelector({\n    container: '#clear-all-selector',\n    // cssClasses: {root, header, body, link, footer}\n    // templates: {header, body, footer}\n    // label: clear all\n    // hideContainerWhenNoRefinements: true\n  })\n);\n```\n\nDefault rendering output:\n\n``` html\n<div class=\"ais-clear-all\">\n  <div class=\"ais-clear-all--header ais-header\">[custom header template]</div>\n  <div class=\"ais-clear-all--body\">\n      <a class=\"ais-clear-all--link\" href={url}>clear all</a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"ais-clear-all--footer ais-footer\">[custom footer template]</div>\n</div>\n```\n\nData passed to the item template:\n- url, in case you want to have a link instead of a button\n- label\n\nPut the onClick on the item template, like it's done for toggle\n",
